network_overview: The 130 ms capture shows a single successful VoLTE IMS registration (SIP REGISTER-100-200) between P-CSCF 10.235.69.1 and S-CSCF 10.235.68.66; no bearer or media traffic is present.

observations.finding: Only 5 packets in 130 ms, all SIP signaling; zero RTP or GTP-U indicates idle UE post-registration
No media streams present; registration completed with 12 ms RTT (100-200), well within 3GPP <200 ms IMS delay budget

recommendations.action: Enable SIP OPTIONS ping from S-CSCF toward registered UE to verify NAT/firewall pin-hole remains open
recommendations.rationale: Prevents 408/Request Timeout on first outbound call when NAT binding times out before T1 expires

recommendations.action: Set SIP Timer T1 = 500 ms and T2 = 4 s on P-CSCF to match LAN RTT <20 ms and reduce retransmission waste
recommendations.rationale: Current defaults (T1=500 ms) are conservative for sub-millisecond core network; tuning cuts setup delay by ~200 ms on every call

recommendations.action: Collect QoS counters (PDR/URR) on Sx interface to confirm QCI=5 bearer is established even when GTP-U is absent in mirror
recommendations.rationale: Ensures IMS signaling EPS bearer is correctly reserved and policed, avoiding silent registration drops

session_analysis.signaling_health: REGISTER transaction completed successfully; no 3xx/4xx/5xx responses, no retransmissions, SCTP association stable
session_analysis.user_plane_health: No GTP or RTP detected; expected for registration-only trace
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Control-plane only; bearer establishment (GTP-C/Sx) occurs before SIP REGISTER but is not mirrored in this capture
